n%20Madhya%20Pradesh%E2%80%99s%20Kuno%20National%20Park%20on%20August%202%2C%20died%20due%20to%20myiasis%20or%20maggot%20infection.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Cheetah%20Conservation%20Fund%20(CCF)%2C%20which%20assists%20Project%20Cheetah%2C%20said%20this%20in%20a%20series%20of%20tweets%20on%20August%203.%20Dhatri%20is%20the%20third%20cheetah%20to%20die%20of%20such%20an%20infection%20in%20the%20Park.%20Post-mortem%20reports%20found%20that%20the%20cause%20of%20death%20of%20cheetahs%20Tejas%20and%20Suraj%20on%20July%2011%20and%2014%20were%20due%20to%20septicaemia.%20The%20animals%20had%20maggot-infested%20wounds%2C%20per%20reports.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EMaggot%20infestation%2C%20again%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FCCFCheetah%2Fstatus%2F1687116755548995584%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eseries%20of%20tweets%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20on%20August%203%2C%20the%20Cheetah%20Conservation%20Fund%20(CCF)%20which%20assists%20Project%20Cheetah%2C%20said%20that%20a%20post-mortem%20revealed%20that%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fninth-cheetah-dies-in-kuno-national-park%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eninth%20cheetah%20that%20was%20found%20dead%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20Kuno%20on%20August%202%20died%20due%20to%20myiasis%2C%20or%20infection%20caused%20by%20fly%20larvae%20(maggots).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECCF%E2%80%99s%20Conservation%20Release%20programme%20manager%2C%20Barth%20Balli%2C%20spent%2010%20days%20tracking%20Dhatri%2C%20a%20female%20from%20Namibia%2C%20to%20get%20close%20enough%20to%20capture%20her%2C%20the%20tweets%20said.%20Though%20he%20could%20not%20capture%20her%20he%20saw%20that%20she%20had%20successfully%20hunted%2C%20it%20added.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20collaboration%20with%20the%20Kuno%20National%20Park%20vet%20team%2C%20CCF%20conducted%20a%20post-mortem%20examination.%20The%20cause%20of%20death%20was%20infection%20due%20to%20maggot%20infestation%20(myiasis)%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20tweet%20said.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20was%20the%20same%20cause%20of%20death%20for%20two%20male%20cheetahs%20and%20the%20reason%20why%20we%20were%20tracking%20Dhatri%20for%20recapture.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20CCF%20added%20that%20authorities%20have%20removed%20collars%20from%20all%20cheetahs%20in%20captivity%20while%20they%20%E2%80%9Cdevelop%20and%20test%20a%20better%20collar%20material%20for%20their%20monitoring%20devices%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAfter%20male%20cheetahs%20Tejas%20and%20Suraj%E2%80%99s%20deaths%20on%20July%2011%20and%2014%2C%20post-mortem%20reports%20revealed%20that%20the%20animals%20had%20died%20due%20to%20%E2%80%9Ctraumatic%20shock%E2%80%9D%20set%20on%20by%20septicaemia.%20Per%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fbhopal%2Fmore-cheetahs-at-kuno-have-neck-wounds-collars-blamed%2Farticleshow%2F101840088.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ereports%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20the%20animals%20had%20maggot-infested%20wounds.%20Experts%20had%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fproject-cheetah-deaths-radio-collar-infections%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Esaid%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20the%20infections%20were%20caused%20by%20the%20radio%20collars%20on%20the%20animals%E2%80%99%20necks.%20However%2C%20the%20National%20Tiger%20Conservation%20Authority%20(NTCA)%20which%20implements%20Project%20Cheetah%20denied%20this%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fauthorities-say-recent-cheetah-deaths-due-to-natural-causes-mp-chief-wildlife-warden-transferred%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Esaid%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20all%20deaths%20have%20been%20due%20to%20%E2%80%9Cnatural%20causes%E2%80%9D.%20However%2C%20authorities%20have%20been%20capturing%20all%20cheetahs%20in%20the%20wild%20in%20Kuno%20to%20monitor%20their%20health.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20their%20tweet%2C%20the%20CCF%20said%20that%20fly%20eggs%20have%20a%20rapid%20incubation%20rate%20and%20the%20larvae%20%E2%80%9Care%20not%20easy%20to%20detect%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThey%20quickly%20reach%20full%20growth%20in%20less%20than%20a%20couple%20%5Bof%5D%20days.%20Myiasis%20also%20occurs%20in%20humans%2C%20and%20is%20common%20in%20rural%20areas%20with%20tropical%20climates%20(India)%20or%20during%20rainy%20seasons%20in%20arid%20climates%20(Namibia).%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EAll%20in%20bomas%20doing%20well%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWith%20Dhatri%E2%80%99s%20death%2C%20there%20is%20only%20one%20more%20cheetah%20in%20the%20wild%20in%20Kuno.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETeams%20are%20working%20to%20bring%20back%20Nirva%2C%20a%20female%20from%20South%20Africa%2C%20for%20%E2%80%9Ccomprehensive%20health%20assessments%20and%20any%20necessary%20treatments%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20CCF%20said.%20It%20added%20that%20all%20the%20other%2014%20cheetahs%20at%20Kuno%20in%20pre-release%20bomas%20%E2%80%93%20seven%20males%2C%20six%20females%2C%20and%20a%20female%20cub%20%E2%80%93%20are%20%E2%80%9Chealthy%20and%20thriving%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThey%20are%20under%20regular%20observation%20by%20our%20expert%20team%20in%20Kuno%2C%E2%80%9D%20their%20tweet%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9COur%20priority%20is%20the%20well-being%20of%20these%20incredible%20animals%2C%20and%20their%20progress%20toward%20successful%20release%20into%20the%20wild%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20tweet%20also%20added.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EStudies%20conducted%20between%202004%20and%202018%20found%20high%20success%20rates%20%E2%80%93%20of%20between%2075-96%25%20%E2%80%93%20of%