20be%20very%20difficult.%20We%20just%20have%20to%20pray%20that%20things%20will%20work%20out.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Economic%20Community%20of%20West%20African%20States%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fecowas%2Ft-66421419%5C%22%3E(ECOWAS)%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0slapped%20severe%20sanctions%20on%20Niger%20on%20Sunday%20in%20response%20to%20the%20coup%2C%20including%20a%20number%20of%20border%20closures.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20impose%20additional%20hardships%20on%20the%20impoverished%20and%20landlocked%20nation%20of%20Niger%2C%20where%20the%20majority%20of%20key%20imports%2C%20including%20food%20staples%20like%20rice%2C%20would%20normally%20be%20trucked%20in%20from%20neighbouring%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EVital%20borders%20still%20closed%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENiger%E2%80%99s%20coup%20leaders%2C%20who%20closed%20all%20land%20borders%20and%20airspace%20when%20they%20took%20control%20on%20July%2026%2C%20announced%20on%20Tuesday%20that%20borders%20to%20some%20neighbours%20were%20reopened.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPeople%20and%20goods%20can%20move%20again%20to%20Algeria%2C%20Libya%20and%20Chad%20%E2%80%94%20who%20aren%E2%80%99t%20in%20ECOWAS%20%E2%80%94%20as%20well%20as%20to%20ECOWAS%20members%20Mali%20and%20Burkina%20Faso%2C%20who%20support%20the%20coup%20leadership.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20key%20borders%20to%20Benin%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fnigeria%2Ft-18943620%5C%22%3ENigeria%3C%2Fa%3E%20remain%20closed%20due%20to%20the%20ECOWAS%20sanctions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Atlantic%20ports%20of%20those%20two%20nations%20are%20vital%20to%20Niger%20for%20the%20import%20and%20export%20of%20goods%2C%C2%A0Abdoul%20Aziz%20Seyni%2C%20an%20economist%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Niamey%2C%20told%20Reuters%20news%20agency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20%E2%80%A6%20aren%E2%80%99t%20a%20country%20with%20direct%20access%20to%20the%20sea%2C%E2%80%9D%20Seyni%20said.%20%E2%80%9CEveryth