ped%20approach%2C%20provided%20them%20with%20valuable%20discipline%20and%20perspective.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBeing%2040-year-olds%2C%20we%20have%20helped%20scale%20many%20companies%20and%20products.%20We%20used%20this%20experience%20and%20maturity%20when%20we%20started%20our%20business.%20It%20was%20a%20calculated%20risk.%20Not%20getting%20investment%2C%20in%20the%20beginning%2C%20was%20actually%20a%20blessing%20for%20us.%20We%20built%20a%20business%20model%20that%20was%20inherently%20profitable%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Rahul.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20advises%20budding%20entrepreneurs%20not%20to%20be%20swayed%20by%20the%20allure%20of%20startups.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CEveryone%20thinks%20that%20starting%20your%20own%20company%20is%20glamorous.%20It%E2%80%99s%20not.%20There%20is%20nothing%20wrong%20with%20having%20a%20regular%20nine-to-five%20job.%20And%20even%20when%20you%20decide%20to%20start%20out%2C%20don%E2%80%99t%20build%20a%20company%20that%20survives%20on%20VC%20money.%20That%20is%20a%20dangerous%20business%20model%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20shares.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Priyanka%20Aeron%2C%20India%20Managing%20Director%20and%20Head%20of%20Global%20HR%20%26amp%3B%20Tech%2C%20swears%20by%20the%20philosophy%20%E2%80%94%20%E2%80%9CWe%20do%20not%20inherit%20the%20earth%20from%20our%20parents%3B%20we%20borrow%20it%20from%20our%20children.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COur%20extensive%20range%20of%20home%20essentials%20embraces%20our%20idea%20that%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20own%20the%20Earth.%20We%20are%20merely%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F325564%2Fthe-disposal-company-bhagyashree-bhansali-waste-plastic-credit-recycle-mumbai-delhi%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eborrowing%20it%20from%20the%20future%20generation%3C%2Fa%3E.%20So%2C%20even%20if%20it%E2%80%99s%20for%20the%20long%20haul%2C%20easier%20yet%20impactful%20changes%20can%20go%20a%20long%20way%20in%20altering%20our%20carbon%20footprint%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EIf%20you%20wish%20to%20explore%20their%20sustainable%20products%2C%20you%20can%20visit%20the%20official%20website%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fecosoulhome.in%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ehere%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEdited%20by%20Pranita%20Bhat%3B%20All%20pictures%20courtesy%3A%20Rahul%20Singh%2C%20EcoSoul%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691070457000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2Fecosoul-1691067035.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D326200%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Entrepreneurs%20Rahul%20Singh%20and%20Arvind%20Ganesan%20started%20EcoSoul%20Home%20to%20provide%20sustainable%20alternatives%20to%20single-use%20plastic.%20With%20tableware%20made%20of%20palm%20leaf%20and%20sugarcane%20bagasse%2C%20they%20have%20now%20built%20a%20business%20on%20track%20to%20clock%20%2450%20million%20in%20revenue.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Sowmya%20Mani%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F326200%2Fecosoul-home-india-boston-sustainable-plastic-free-kitchenware-cutlery-sugarcane-palm%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80%98They%20Call%20it%20a%20Man%E2%80%99s%20Job%E2%80%99%3A%20The%20Lives%20%26%20Tribulations%20of%204%20Women%20Who%20Cremate%20Unclaimed%20Bodies%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ETrigger%20Warning%3A%20Graphic%20mentions%20of%20death%2C%20blood%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENearly%20two%20months%20ago%2C%20when%20Odisha%E2%80%99s%20Madhusmita%20Prusty%20was%20leaving%20for%20work%20at%208%3A30%20in%20the%20morning%2C%20she%20received%20a%20call%20from%20the%20Government%20Railway%20Police%20(GRP).%20It%20was%20to%20inform%20her%20about%20the%20unfortunate%20Odisha%20triple%20train%20accident%2C%20which%20had%20claimed%20the%20lives%20of%20295%20passengers%20in%20a%20matter%20of%20minutes%20the%20previous%20night.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20noon%20on%20June%203%2C%20the%20Bhubneswar%20resident%20reached%20Balasore%20along%20with%20three%20other%20women%20%E2%80%94%20Smita%20Mohanty%2C%20Swagatika%20Rao%2C%20and%20Snehanjali%20Sethi%20%E2%80%94%20in%20their%20ambulance.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERecalling%20the%20episode%2C%20Madhusmita%20tells%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20situation%20there%20was%20very%20unsettling.%20Blood%20was%20everywhere.%20Some%20were%20lying%20without%20limbs.%20The%20injured%20were%20crying%20for%20help.%20If%20we%20carried%20somebody%20to%20take%20them%20to%20the%20hospital%2C%20others%20would%20insist%20that%20we%20take%20them%20first.%20It%20was%20so%20hard%20for%20us%2C%20we%20did%20not%20know%20where%20to%20begin.%20It%20was%20a%20very%20emotional%20state%20for%20us.%20Their%20cries%20still%20echo%20in%20our%20ears.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201040px)%20100vw%2C%201040px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2FWhatsApp-Image-2023-07-31-at-12.48.53-AM-1691066305.jpeg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221040%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Madhusmita%20was%20joined%20by%20Smita%2C%20Swagatika%2C%20and%20Snehanjali%20in%20the%20initiative.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2FWhatsApp-Image-2023-07-31-at-12.48.53-AM-1691066305.jpeg%201040w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2FWhatsApp-Image-2023-07-31-at-12.48.53-AM-1691066305-300x225.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2FWhatsApp-Image-2023-07-31-at-12.48.53-AM-1691066305-500x375.jpeg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.c